AraC protein can activate transcription from only one position and when pointed in only one direction .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9440505" target="_blank">9440505</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8980677" target="_blank">8980677</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10715008" target="_blank">10715008</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7768852" target="_blank">7768852</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9409145" target="_blank">9409145</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9600836" target="_blank">9600836</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9371449" target="_blank">9371449</a>, <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8396120" target="_blank">8396120</a>]<br></label>
