<li>For induction , all three operons require ( a ) the L-arabinose-specific positive regulatory protein , AraC ( b ) the catabolite gene activator protein ( CAP ; also referred to as the cAMP receptor protein , CRP ) , ( c ) and cAMP ( Greenblatt and Schleif 1971 ; Englesberg and Wil-cox 1974 ; Lee et al. 1974 ; Kolodrubetz and Schleif 1981 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2997582" target="_blank">2997582</a>]<br></li>
<li>One operon , araFGH , codes for the well-studied AraC protein and by cyclic AMP ( cAMPt ) receptor protein ( CRP ) ( Englesberg et al. , 1965 ; Greenblatt & Schleif , 1971 ; Wilcox et al. , 1974 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2231717" target="_blank">2231717</a>]<br></li>
