<li>Transcription activation by AraC has been studied intensively ( reviewed in 9,10 ) and serves as a model for activation by other proteins of the family .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12060687" target="_blank">12060687</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , in contrast to MelR , N-terminal deletions in AraC give truncated proteins competent for inducer-independent transcription activation ( 11 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7784205" target="_blank">7784205</a>]<br></li>
<li>Consistent with this , Bustos and Schleif ( 3 ) showed that the isolated AraC C terminal is competent for this activation .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16621812" target="_blank">16621812</a>]<br></li>
<li>S3 in the supplemental material ) , indicating that either AraC has only a minor effect on ytfQ expression or that more substantial regulation by AraC is associated with other growth conditions .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>However , we detected no effect of GalR on regulation of ytfQ by AraC ( data not shown ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>by the weaker and tightly regulated PBAD -- AraC system ŽGuzman et al. , 1995 .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11311395" target="_blank">11311395</a>]<br></li>
<li>Its expression is regulated by three XylS/AraC family regulators , MarA , SoxS and Rob .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12791142" target="_blank">12791142</a>]<br></li>
<li>pTolAIII derivative expression was regulated by the AraC ( TolAIII1 and TolAIII2 ) or LacI ( TolAIII3 ) repressor .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11851406" target="_blank">11851406</a>]<br></li>
<li>Although we have no structural data for MelR , its domain organization appears to be similar to AraC ( Fig. 2 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16621812" target="_blank">16621812</a>]<br></li>
<li>Elucidation of the structural details of many of the important , functional , intramolecular interactions in AraC requires high resolution structural information .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19422057" target="_blank">19422057</a>]<br></li>
<li>Saviola B , Seabold R , Schleif R. Arm-domain interactions in AraC .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=19422057" target="_blank">19422057</a>]<br></li>
