<li>How is AraC able to activate p in this FGH atypical arrangement ?	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=7768852" target="_blank">7768852</a>]<br></li>
<li>We did not detect regulation of polB by AraC in S. enterica .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>Hence , polB regulation by AraC may be widely conserved .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>and almost full induction of paAD is achieved when AraC is overexpressed .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1848302" target="_blank">1848302</a>]<br></li>
<li>AraC was added to a ® nal concentration between 1 and 100 nM .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9600836" target="_blank">9600836</a>]<br></li>
<li>DN AraC Dual effects regulon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=1943993" target="_blank">1943993</a>]<br></li>
<li>AraC is the major transcriptional-regulator of the regulon .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10094697" target="_blank">10094697</a>]<br></li>
