<li>First , AraC binds strongly to the single target I1 in vitro only in the presence of L-arabinose ; in its absence , binding is reduced about sixfold ( see Figures 4 ( a ) and ( c ) , 7 ( b ) and ( d ) ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8980677" target="_blank">8980677</a>]<br></li>
<li>AraC positively regulates transcription of the four other operons in the presence of arabinose and represses transcription in its absence ( 34 , 35 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10094697" target="_blank">10094697</a>]<br></li>
