<li>How , then , can AraC assist in the activation of transcription at pFGH when pointed in what is apparently the wrong direction and when located in what are apparently the wrong places ?	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10715008" target="_blank">10715008</a>]<br></li>
<li>The importance of aligned residues AraC R251 and RhaR T279 in their respective mechanisms , however , suggests that the AraC and RhaR mechanisms may share the common principle of preventing contacts with σ70 in the absence of effector .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18366439" target="_blank">18366439</a>]<br></li>
<li>Further , if these s70 residues are important for activation by RhaS in the absence of CRP , it is possible that other AraC / XylS family proteins that activate transcription without the aid of a second activator , such as CRP , may also require these residues .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10940041" target="_blank">10940041</a>]<br></li>
<li>The lack of defect from 70 K593A , R599A , or R608A at the ( rhaS-lacZ ) 216 promoter is similar to previous ﬁndings with RhaS and AraC that substitutions at 70 some residues were defective only in the absence of CRP activation ( 4 , 27 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=15342598" target="_blank">15342598</a>]<br></li>
<li>The more recent ﬁnding that other s70 substitutions at positions near R596 , especially K593A , signiﬁcantly reduce activation by AraC in the absence of CRP supports the hypothesis that wild-type AraC and s70 make an interaction that contributes to transcription-activation ( 36 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=10940041" target="_blank">10940041</a>]<br></li>
<li>In the XylS regulator , the ﬁrst HTH motif is located at positions 228 to 251 and the second HTH motif is located at positions 281 to 305 ; these correspond to positions 195 to 218 and 245 to 270 , respectively , in the AraC regulator ( 26 -- 28 , 169 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9409145" target="_blank">9409145</a>]<br></li>
