<li>Conservation of the AraC regulon across the family Entero-bacteriaceae .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>AraC is highly conserved across the family Entero-bacteriaceae , which includes E. coli and S. enterica .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=24272778" target="_blank">24272778</a>]<br></li>
<li>As far as we know , this is the ﬁrst published study in which such a reagent has been used to investigate proteins of the AraC family .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12675795" target="_blank">12675795</a>]<br></li>
