<li>AraC and XylS , the namesakes of the family , are examples of two-domain family members in which the nonfamily domain functions in both effector binding and dimerization ( 7 , 19 , 33 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17513476" target="_blank">17513476</a>]<br></li>
<li>SoxS protein is homologous to the C-terminal region of transcriptional regulators of the AraC family ( Wu and Weiss , 1991 ; Amabile-Cuevas and Demple , 1991 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=8899708" target="_blank">8899708</a>]<br></li>
