<li>Regarding carbon metabolism , members of the family control the degradation of sugars such as arabinose ( AraC ) , cellobiose ( CelD ) , melibiose ( MelR and MsmR ) , rafﬁnose ( RafR and MsmR ) , rhamnose ( RhaR and RhaS ) , and xylose ( XylR ) ; certain amino acids such as valine ( MmsR ) , arginine ( AdiY ) , and ornithine ( OruR ) ; alcohols such as 1,2-propanediol ( PocR ) ; alkylbenzoates ( XylS ) ; p-hydroxyphenylacetic acid ( HpaA ) ; and herbicides such as S-ethyl dipropylthiocarbamate ( TchR ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=9409145" target="_blank">9409145</a>]<br></li>
<li>Indole signaling for mdtEF expression is independent of the EvgSA pathway but mediated by GadX , which is also an AraC / XylS regulator that cooperates with YdeO ( 5 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=16885453" target="_blank">16885453</a>]<br></li>
<li>Alternative loop formation also plays a role in the regulation of araBAD and araC expression by the AraC regulatory protein ( 9 , 20 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=2211510" target="_blank">2211510</a>]<br></li>
